WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:02.961
<i>Previously on "The Rookie"...</i>

00:02.961 --> 00:04.254
Lucy:
What's Metro doing here?

00:04.254 --> 00:05.047
Metro would be
a good fit for Tim.

00:05.047 --> 00:06.465
There's an opening
in Metro.

00:06.465 --> 00:08.383
Lieutenant Pine just called me,
and I'm going over.

00:08.383 --> 00:09.426
That's great.

00:09.426 --> 00:10.469
Monica.
What are you doing here?

00:10.469 --> 00:11.678
Elijah Stone is my client.

00:11.678 --> 00:12.888
Del Monte:
Elijah's attorney?

00:12.888 --> 00:13.972
We used to be engaged.

00:13.972 --> 00:15.599
Hi.
I'm his mother.

00:15.599 --> 00:16.642
Nolan: The boxes?

00:16.642 --> 00:18.185
Your mother sold me
snake oil?

00:18.185 --> 00:20.020
This is my boss' wife.

00:20.020 --> 00:22.147
Do you have any idea what this
could do to my career?

00:22.147 --> 00:23.398
Goodbye.

00:23.398 --> 00:28.195
♪♪

00:28.195 --> 00:30.239
Celina:
Alright. Turn to your left.

00:30.239 --> 00:32.407
[ Camera shutter clicks ]
Turn to your right.

00:32.407 --> 00:33.825
You know, the boardwalk
is a public place.

00:33.825 --> 00:35.285
I have a right to perform.

00:35.285 --> 00:36.370
Well, it does not
give you the right

00:36.370 --> 00:39.414
to pick your
audience's pockets.

00:39.414 --> 00:41.583
[ Chuckles ] You know
I can get out of these, right?

00:41.583 --> 00:43.752
You can try.

00:43.752 --> 00:45.379
[ Handcuffs clicking,
chain rattling ]

00:45.379 --> 00:48.423
Voilà.
I'm a master escape artist.

00:48.423 --> 00:53.011
♪♪

00:53.011 --> 00:55.138
Cute. Let's go.

00:55.138 --> 00:57.349
Gil: You know,
no cage can hold me.

00:57.349 --> 00:59.434
Yeah?
[ Buzzer ]

00:59.434 --> 01:00.477
Alright.

01:00.477 --> 01:02.646
What about this cage?

01:02.646 --> 01:06.066
A magician
is always prepared.

01:06.066 --> 01:07.651
[ Flame hisses ]
[ Gasps ]

01:07.651 --> 01:09.319
[ Men coughing ]

01:12.990 --> 01:14.866
How did you think
that was gonna work?

01:14.866 --> 01:16.410
Yeah. No.
I didn't get that far.

01:16.410 --> 01:19.746
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh,
oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

01:19.746 --> 01:24.459
♪ I'm gonna win for you
like I know you want me to do ♪

01:26.378 --> 01:27.671
Nolan: [ In distance ]
No. You said that already.

01:27.671 --> 01:29.673
And I already
explained it to you.

01:33.218 --> 01:36.555
That's ridiculous.

01:36.555 --> 01:38.932
No. Absolutely not.

01:38.932 --> 01:40.267
No. I'm done.

01:40.267 --> 01:41.518
No --

01:41.518 --> 01:42.853
I am done.

01:42.853 --> 01:45.397
Your mom?

01:45.397 --> 01:46.523
How'd you know?
[ Sighs ]

01:46.523 --> 01:48.442
Your shoulders
are touching your ears.

01:48.442 --> 01:49.735
What's the latest?

01:49.735 --> 01:51.069
She is, uh, devastated

01:51.069 --> 01:52.571
that she hasn't been
invited to the wedding.

01:52.571 --> 01:54.197
Did you tell her we're
not doing a big thing?

01:54.197 --> 01:55.657
We literally have
two guests.

01:55.657 --> 01:56.908
Explained all that.
Doesn't matter.

01:56.908 --> 01:58.493
Still a knife
through her heart.

01:58.493 --> 02:00.329
Look, if it helps,
I don't mind inviting her.

02:00.329 --> 02:03.165
No. No way. No. It's...

02:03.165 --> 02:04.333
It's not even
about the wedding.

02:04.333 --> 02:07.878
She wants me to pay her
not to come -- $10,000.

02:07.878 --> 02:09.212
What?
I know.

02:09.212 --> 02:10.964
Don't worry.
She is not coming.

02:10.964 --> 02:13.008
I will not let her
ruin our wedding.

02:13.008 --> 02:14.176
Mm.

02:20.807 --> 02:22.059
[ Exhales softly ]

02:23.810 --> 02:26.146
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

02:26.146 --> 02:27.606
♪♪

02:27.606 --> 02:28.899
Did I miss it?

02:28.899 --> 02:30.859
It's cute.
[ Chuckles ]

02:30.859 --> 02:32.277
Why are you up so early?

02:32.277 --> 02:34.780
I was gonna get a photo
of your reaction.

02:34.780 --> 02:36.406
There's a Metro
training today.

02:36.406 --> 02:37.866
As the newbie, it's my job

02:37.866 --> 02:39.785
to, uh, haul in the gear
and the ammo.

02:39.785 --> 02:41.453
Yeah, the newbie.

02:41.453 --> 02:43.038
The boot.

02:43.038 --> 02:44.831
I'm a sergeant.
Mnh-mnh.

02:44.831 --> 02:46.958
You're still a boot
in my book.

02:46.958 --> 02:49.086
[ Door opens ]
Oh. Hey.

02:49.086 --> 02:51.004
Are you
just getting home?

02:51.004 --> 02:52.589
Must've been
a heck of a party.

02:52.589 --> 02:55.175
Yeah. Rager.

02:55.175 --> 02:56.843
Mm.

02:56.843 --> 02:58.136
Did I interrupt something?

02:58.136 --> 03:00.222
No. No,
I-I was just heading out.

03:00.222 --> 03:01.640
Uh, can't be late
on my first day.

03:01.640 --> 03:03.058
Mm-hmm.

03:03.058 --> 03:05.310
Bye.
Hey.

03:05.310 --> 03:06.978
You're gonna
be great today.

03:06.978 --> 03:08.980
Knock 'em dead.

03:08.980 --> 03:10.315
Bye.

03:14.695 --> 03:16.154
Good morning.

03:16.154 --> 03:17.864
[ Scoffs ] Whatever.
He is!

03:19.032 --> 03:21.243
Well, of course you'd say that.
Because it's the truth.

03:21.243 --> 03:22.661
Like you've ever
cared about the truth.

03:22.661 --> 03:23.954
Okay, that's enough.

03:23.954 --> 03:25.455
I'd ask where this animosity
is coming from,

03:25.455 --> 03:26.706
but I have an idea.

03:26.706 --> 03:28.083
Okay, this has nothing
to do with our past

03:28.083 --> 03:29.501
and everything to do
with the law.

03:29.501 --> 03:32.212
Let's focus on the law,
then, shall we?

03:32.212 --> 03:33.964
You're presenting
a motion to exclude.

03:33.964 --> 03:35.006
Yes, Your Honor.

03:35.006 --> 03:36.508
You disagree.

03:36.508 --> 03:38.677
Mr. Parker is an eyewitness
to this crime.

03:38.677 --> 03:40.220
He picked the shooter
out of a lineup.

03:40.220 --> 03:42.722
His testimony is essential
to this case.

03:42.722 --> 03:44.224
Ms. Stevens.

03:44.224 --> 03:47.060
You know as well as anyone
eyewitness testimony is flawed,

03:47.060 --> 03:49.229
and this witness
had a gun pointed at him.

03:49.229 --> 03:52.732
High levels of stress
negatively impact memory.

03:52.732 --> 03:54.943
Okay, but any eyewitness
to a crime

03:54.943 --> 03:57.154
has experienced
high levels of stress.

03:57.154 --> 03:59.739
Are we throwing out
the very notion of witnesses?

03:59.739 --> 04:01.533
Do not put words
in my mouth.

04:01.533 --> 04:04.119
Okay.
[ Clears throat ]

04:04.119 --> 04:06.413
I'm inclined to side with Monica
on this one.

04:06.413 --> 04:08.206
I'm excluding
his testimony.

04:08.206 --> 04:10.834
Wha-- On -- On what grounds?
That's absurd.

04:10.834 --> 04:12.669
Watch yourself.

04:12.669 --> 04:14.713
I'm sorry.

04:14.713 --> 04:18.383
I meant no disrespect.
Um...

04:18.383 --> 04:20.594
I'm gonna need a few minutes
to confer with my team.

04:20.594 --> 04:22.095
Good idea.

04:26.308 --> 04:29.060
[ Door opens ]

04:29.060 --> 04:30.520
Thank you.

04:30.520 --> 04:37.402
♪♪

04:37.402 --> 04:40.030
Metro Cop: [ Through headset ]
<i>Okay, you have an active</i>
<i>shooter still at large.</i>

04:40.030 --> 04:42.532
<i>Your job is to locate the</i>
<i>suspect and stop the threat.</i>

04:42.532 --> 04:50.081
♪♪

04:50.081 --> 04:57.756
♪♪

04:57.756 --> 04:59.174
Mad Dog: <i>Bang. You're dead.</i>
<i>You're telegraphing.</i>

04:59.174 --> 05:00.342
<i>You're dead. Bang. Dead.</i>

05:00.342 --> 05:02.427
<i>You're dead. Dead.</i>
<i>Bang. Dead.</i>

05:02.427 --> 05:05.430
Bradford, this isn't patrol.
This is Metro.

05:05.430 --> 05:07.933
Major crimes, terrorism,
barricades, hostages.

05:07.933 --> 05:09.601
We are an elite unit.

05:09.601 --> 05:12.020
Your form's got to be
perfect, man.

05:12.020 --> 05:14.773
Alright.
Let's take 10.

05:14.773 --> 05:16.608
[ Sighs ] What, there's only
one way to clear a room?

05:16.608 --> 05:18.318
That's news to me,

05:18.318 --> 05:19.986
'cause I've actually done this
a million times successfully.

05:19.986 --> 05:21.238
Don't worry.
Happens to everyone.

05:21.238 --> 05:23.615
Metro takes
some getting used to.

05:23.615 --> 05:26.117
You'll get it.

05:26.117 --> 05:28.161
Harper: That is the dumbest
ruling I've ever heard.

05:28.161 --> 05:29.704
Yeah, I agree.

05:29.704 --> 05:31.373
But we're gonna
have to make this case

05:31.373 --> 05:33.083
without Parker's testimony.

05:33.083 --> 05:35.418
Do you really think
the jury will convict without?

05:35.418 --> 05:37.003
No. I'm filing
for a continuance.

05:37.003 --> 05:38.213
My team needs to regroup.

05:38.213 --> 05:40.465
Well, I guess
I'm not testifying today.

05:40.465 --> 05:42.050
Oh, it's just as well.

05:42.050 --> 05:43.885
I was gonna have to
hand this one over to you.

05:43.885 --> 05:45.804
Well, there's nothing
like a baby to win over a jury.

05:45.804 --> 05:48.223
Oh, well, we're gonna need
all the help we can get

05:48.223 --> 05:49.850
without that testimony.

05:49.850 --> 05:52.602
Didn't something similar happen
in one of Lopez's cases?

05:52.602 --> 05:54.229
Just like last month.

05:54.229 --> 05:56.565
I'm never assigned to anything
she's investigated.

05:56.565 --> 05:58.191
I remember she was pissed.

05:58.191 --> 06:00.318
She handed your office
a perfect case.

06:00.318 --> 06:03.655
Practically had a bow on it,
and then it fell apart in trial.

06:03.655 --> 06:04.739
It was the same judge.

06:04.739 --> 06:05.991
Well, judges can be fickle.

06:05.991 --> 06:07.409
It's hard to predict
how they'll rule.

06:07.409 --> 06:10.704
But Rivas has been solid
until recently.

06:10.704 --> 06:12.622
True.

06:12.622 --> 06:14.332
You know, I clerked for him
back when I was starting out.

06:14.332 --> 06:15.709
Monica and I both did.

06:15.709 --> 06:16.960
Mind like a scalpel.

06:16.960 --> 06:18.545
Yeah, but he is
getting older.

06:18.545 --> 06:20.046
I mean, if he's
starting to slip,

06:20.046 --> 06:22.883
someone should talk to him
about retiring.

06:22.883 --> 06:25.468
I mean,
maybe a former clerk

06:25.468 --> 06:27.679
who knows how
to cushion the blow.

06:27.679 --> 06:29.014
[ Leah crying ]

06:29.014 --> 06:30.307
Oh. Sorry.

06:30.307 --> 06:31.975
Can't stop,
not even for a second.

06:31.975 --> 06:33.476
It's okay.
I've literally been there.

06:33.476 --> 06:34.811
You go.
I'll deal with Rivas.

06:34.811 --> 06:36.354
Thank you.
Yeah.

06:36.354 --> 06:39.566
[ Leah crying ]
Yes, well, what is going on?

06:39.566 --> 06:42.193
Hm.
[ Elevator bell dings ]

06:42.193 --> 06:45.697
Oh! Hey. I just heard
of a new place to try for lunch.

06:45.697 --> 06:48.658
It's Chinese-
Ukrainian fusion.

06:48.658 --> 06:49.951
Is it cheap?

06:49.951 --> 06:52.162
No. But --
What? You're rich.

06:52.162 --> 06:53.580
No, my parents are rich, okay?

06:53.580 --> 06:55.332
And I'm not gonna take
any more of their money.

06:55.332 --> 06:57.167
Since when?

06:57.167 --> 06:58.877
Since my mom
showed me a prototype

06:58.877 --> 07:00.837
of a new Aaron Thorsen
action figure.

07:00.837 --> 07:03.715
Wha-- That sounds awesome.
No, look, I worked hard

07:03.715 --> 07:05.967
to have people
take me seriously as a cop.

07:05.967 --> 07:08.136
I'm not gonna undermine it
for a couple million dollars.

07:08.136 --> 07:09.179
Hold on. I'm sorry.

07:09.179 --> 07:10.597
A couple <i>million?</i>
Yeah.

07:10.597 --> 07:12.432
Dude, if you're
not gonna do it, I will.

07:12.432 --> 07:15.644
Lucy Chen, Fist of Justice.

07:15.644 --> 07:18.188
What are you doing?
Hi.

07:18.188 --> 07:20.523
I'm, uh -- I'm working
on my side hustle.

07:20.523 --> 07:22.567
Oh. What's on your head?

07:22.567 --> 07:25.236
You have a -- You have
a little something on your head.

07:25.236 --> 07:26.655
Uh, no.
It's -- It's nothing.

07:26.655 --> 07:29.449
I just need to get situated
into my new office.

07:29.449 --> 07:32.327
Aaron: Metro-Police liaison.
Best of both worlds.

07:32.327 --> 07:33.536
That's right.

07:33.536 --> 07:38.958
♪♪

07:38.958 --> 07:41.294
Well, at least it won't
take too long to move in.

07:41.294 --> 07:43.004
No.
[ Giggles ]

07:43.004 --> 07:44.964
♪♪

07:44.964 --> 07:46.633
[ Sighing ] Alright.

07:46.633 --> 07:54.391
♪♪

07:54.391 --> 07:56.059
She's your mom.

07:56.059 --> 07:58.228
I mean, how can you not have
your mom at your wedding?

07:58.228 --> 08:00.980
She's a narcissist
and a borderline con woman.

08:00.980 --> 08:03.733
She tried to fleece
Sergeant Grey.
Okay, that's not good.

08:03.733 --> 08:05.860
And not even close
to the worst thing she's done.

08:05.860 --> 08:06.986
Yeah,
but she's your mom.

08:06.986 --> 08:08.530
Look, my mom's challenging,

08:08.530 --> 08:10.490
but I can't imagine
getting married without her.

08:10.490 --> 08:11.700
Which probably means

08:11.700 --> 08:14.119
I'll have to get married
in her living room.

08:14.119 --> 08:16.830
[ Chuckles ] Look,
I run into this all the time.

08:16.830 --> 08:19.499
You have
a fundamentally good mom,

08:19.499 --> 08:21.668
so of course
you can't imagine my situation.

08:21.668 --> 08:23.128
You're right.

08:23.128 --> 08:25.505
I don't know what you've
dealt with. I shouldn't judge.

08:25.505 --> 08:26.881
Ace: I will.

08:26.881 --> 08:28.800
She's your mother.

08:28.800 --> 08:30.093
She gave you life, man.

08:30.093 --> 08:31.720
We caught you trying to pawn
your mother's jewelry

08:31.720 --> 08:33.596
to buy drugs.
You don't get an opinion.

08:33.596 --> 08:37.016
♪♪

08:37.016 --> 08:40.019
Aaron: Seriously, how do you
live on a cop's salary?

08:40.019 --> 08:42.105
It's not that bad.
I mean, we make good money.

08:42.105 --> 08:44.315
My paycheck just evaporates.

08:44.315 --> 08:46.484
I mean, my dry-cleaning bill
alone is $500 a week.

08:46.484 --> 08:47.986
How are we supposed
to afford that?

08:47.986 --> 08:49.404
We're not.

08:49.404 --> 08:52.073
W-What are you dry-cleaning?
Your jeans?

08:52.073 --> 08:53.116
Everything.

08:53.116 --> 08:54.617
Aaron...

08:54.617 --> 08:56.077
do you know
how to do your laundry?

08:56.077 --> 08:57.704
Laundry ruins your clothes.

08:57.704 --> 09:00.290
Dry cleaning is the most
cost-effective in the long run.

09:00.290 --> 09:02.333
What -- Who --
Where did you hear that?

09:02.333 --> 09:03.501
My mom.

09:03.501 --> 09:06.087
[ Cellphone ringing ]

09:06.087 --> 09:07.505
Hey, what's up?

09:07.505 --> 09:10.759
I'm at my babysitting job,
and things are weird.

09:10.759 --> 09:13.720
Cosmo says when he woke up,
both of his parents were gone,

09:13.720 --> 09:15.597
and now no one's
answering their phone.

09:15.597 --> 09:16.848
Okay.
We'll be right there.

09:16.848 --> 09:18.141
[ Cellphone clicks ]

09:29.611 --> 09:30.904
Thanks for coming.

09:30.904 --> 09:32.572
Lucy: Yeah, of course.

09:32.572 --> 09:34.115
Cosmo's in here.

09:37.827 --> 09:39.621
These are the cops
I was telling you about.

09:39.621 --> 09:40.455
Hi.

09:40.455 --> 09:41.831
You good?

09:41.831 --> 09:43.083
How's the cereal?

09:43.083 --> 09:44.334
Mm, it's cereal.

09:44.334 --> 09:46.336
Hey, I offered you
unicorn cloud bread.

09:46.336 --> 09:48.338
You're the one
who wanted Wheetie Bran.

09:48.338 --> 09:49.923
Weirdo.

09:49.923 --> 09:51.466
Can I play on the Switch?

09:51.466 --> 09:52.717
Go ahead.

09:56.054 --> 09:57.097
How's he doing?

09:57.097 --> 09:58.973
He hasn't said much.

09:58.973 --> 10:01.601
I know he's scared. He just
doesn't want to admit it.

10:01.601 --> 10:04.729
Did you notice any signs of
forced entry when you got here?

10:04.729 --> 10:06.773
No. I-I used my key
to get in.

10:06.773 --> 10:09.192
I looked around for a little.
Everything seems normal.

10:09.192 --> 10:10.485
No broken windows
or anything.

10:10.485 --> 10:11.820
How well
do you know the family?

10:11.820 --> 10:14.697
I've been working here
for six months.

10:14.697 --> 10:17.575
The dad's a little aloof.
He works a lot.

10:17.575 --> 10:18.910
Some investment thing.

10:18.910 --> 10:20.411
The mom's around more.

10:20.411 --> 10:22.122
She runs a non-profit.

10:22.122 --> 10:23.957
Alright, well, we'll check
with their employers.

10:23.957 --> 10:25.625
[ Door opens, closes ]

10:25.625 --> 10:27.377
Mr. Laetner.
I've been calling you.

10:27.377 --> 10:28.878
You called the police.

10:28.878 --> 10:30.505
Sorry, uh, yeah, um...

10:30.505 --> 10:32.173
I couldn't find anyone.
I was scared.

10:32.173 --> 10:34.717
I'm so sorry.
It's all been so crazy.

10:34.717 --> 10:37.178
We had a family emergency.
My wife had to fly home

10:37.178 --> 10:38.805
to deal with an aunt
who had a heart attack.

10:38.805 --> 10:41.516
I should have told you.
It...completely slipped my mind.

10:41.516 --> 10:43.393
Where did you say
your wife was?

10:43.393 --> 10:44.936
Cincinnati.

10:44.936 --> 10:47.438
Uh, she probably forgot
her phone charger. Typical.

10:47.438 --> 10:49.399
This is all
a-a big misunderstanding.

10:49.399 --> 10:51.985
And where were you?
Your son woke up alone.

10:51.985 --> 10:53.736
I...took her
to the airport.

10:53.736 --> 10:56.406
I thought I could get back
before he woke up.

10:56.406 --> 10:57.615
Is he okay?

10:57.615 --> 10:59.534
He's fine.
He's in his room.

10:59.534 --> 11:01.202
I'll go talk to him.

11:01.202 --> 11:03.246
I'm so sorry
you came out for nothing.

11:03.246 --> 11:06.499
Well, we need to talk to your
wife to, uh, verify she's okay.

11:06.499 --> 11:07.792
It's protocol.

11:07.792 --> 11:09.377
You understand, right?
Right.

11:09.377 --> 11:11.963
Um, I'll get you
her aunt's number.

11:11.963 --> 11:13.256
I know I have it somewhere.

11:13.256 --> 11:15.008
Here.

11:15.008 --> 11:16.968
Just give us her full name
and approximate age,

11:16.968 --> 11:18.178
and we'll find it.

11:18.178 --> 11:19.596
Of course.
[ Chuckles ]

11:19.596 --> 11:21.222
Should I take Cosmo
to school?

11:21.222 --> 11:23.683
You know what? He's missed
half the day already.

11:23.683 --> 11:25.143
Can you stay
and look after him?

11:25.143 --> 11:27.103
No problem.
Great.

11:27.103 --> 11:30.023
Again, I'm so sorry
we wasted your time.

11:30.023 --> 11:32.817
I'll see you later.

11:32.817 --> 11:34.027
You buying that?

11:34.027 --> 11:35.361
Not a word.

11:35.361 --> 11:37.363
We should loop in
the detectives.

11:37.363 --> 11:39.449
Hey. I'm taking a poll.

11:39.449 --> 11:41.492
How old were you when you did
your first load of laundry?

11:41.492 --> 11:43.369
Bailey: Ooh. No idea.

11:43.369 --> 11:45.705
I was living at home, though,
so...14?

11:45.705 --> 11:48.625
Okay, Aaron's answer was never.
He was never years old.

11:48.625 --> 11:49.751
What?

11:49.751 --> 11:51.502
<i>He doesn't know how.</i>

11:51.502 --> 11:53.838
[ Chuckles ] I don't know
why I should be so shocked.

11:53.838 --> 11:55.089
What about you?

11:55.089 --> 11:56.966
6. I learned early
my mom wasn't gonna do it.

11:56.966 --> 11:58.426
Also not shocking.

11:58.426 --> 11:59.886
Alright, well,
I got to go, babe.

11:59.886 --> 12:01.054
I'll see you later at lunch.

12:01.054 --> 12:02.555
Yeah, wouldn't miss it.

12:02.555 --> 12:04.265
[ Cellphone clicks ]

12:04.265 --> 12:06.059
It is a good thing
you wore a helmet.

12:06.059 --> 12:07.185
I think you're gonna be fine.

12:07.185 --> 12:09.062
[ Gunshots, glass breaking ]
Tom: Aah!

12:09.062 --> 12:10.688
[ Horn blares ]

12:10.688 --> 12:12.732
[ Gunshots ]

12:12.732 --> 12:15.109
♪♪

12:15.109 --> 12:18.571
[ Tires squealing ]

12:18.571 --> 12:20.531
[ Engine revs ]

12:20.531 --> 12:25.495
♪♪

12:25.495 --> 12:30.959
♪♪

12:30.959 --> 12:33.253
[ Bailey grunting ]

12:33.253 --> 12:37.423
♪♪

12:37.423 --> 12:39.259
[ Breathing heavily ]

12:45.723 --> 12:48.810
[ Sirens wailing,
indistinct radio chatter ]

12:48.810 --> 12:52.021
Hey. You hurt?

12:52.021 --> 12:54.732
I'm fine. My partner
just went into surgery.

12:54.732 --> 12:56.317
Who shoots at an ambulance?

12:56.317 --> 12:59.195
I don't know.
I saw a red sedan speeding off.

12:59.195 --> 13:00.989
I wish I could be more helpful.
I'm sorry.

13:00.989 --> 13:03.157
I mean, don't apologize.
You jumped in front

13:03.157 --> 13:04.659
and hit the brakes.
That's badass.

13:04.659 --> 13:06.035
Badass or bad luck?

13:06.035 --> 13:08.413
This is the second partner
I've sent into the hospital.

13:08.413 --> 13:09.789
Well, if you really think
you have bad luck,

13:09.789 --> 13:12.333
I know a great <i>curandera.</i>
She'll cleanse it right out.

13:12.333 --> 13:13.584
I might take you up on that.

13:13.584 --> 13:15.253
Just got word
from the hospital.

13:15.253 --> 13:17.297
Your partner and the patient
are gonna be okay.

13:17.297 --> 13:18.923
[ Sighing ]
Oh, good. Thank you.

13:18.923 --> 13:20.133
They'll have
police escorts

13:20.133 --> 13:21.718
until we figure out
who the target was.

13:21.718 --> 13:23.219
Think they were shooting
at the patient?

13:23.219 --> 13:26.055
It could have just been
a random drive-by. I don't know.

13:26.055 --> 13:27.223
Well, we've got
officers canvassing,

13:27.223 --> 13:28.808
looking for
security footage.

13:28.808 --> 13:30.643
We'll know more soon.

13:30.643 --> 13:33.021
So, when you get done here,
check in with Sergeant Hadley.

13:33.021 --> 13:34.230
She'll be
coordinating the grid.

13:34.230 --> 13:36.065
On it.

13:36.065 --> 13:37.775
I don't suppose you'll be
taking the rest of the day off?

13:37.775 --> 13:39.152
Because I got shot at?

13:39.152 --> 13:41.029
Silly question.
Sorry I asked.

13:41.029 --> 13:41.988
You'll call me
if you need anything?

13:41.988 --> 13:43.156
Thank you. I will.

13:49.787 --> 13:51.873
What's so important you can't
even let me get to my office?

13:51.873 --> 13:53.875
We think Judge Rivas
is on the take.

13:53.875 --> 13:55.251
That's a big accusation.

13:55.251 --> 13:57.420
I know. But I also know him.
I know how his mind works.

13:57.420 --> 13:58.838
And his rulings
have been inconsistent

13:58.838 --> 14:01.716
over the past three months.
And it's not random.

14:01.716 --> 14:04.218
They're all tied and connected
to Monica and her firm.

14:04.218 --> 14:06.429
He overwhelmingly
rules in her favor.

14:06.429 --> 14:09.432
So you think she's bribing the
judge to protect Elijah's guys?

14:09.432 --> 14:11.350
With Elijah
writing the checks,

14:11.350 --> 14:14.103
she's under tremendous pressure
to bring results.

14:14.103 --> 14:16.522
I wouldn't put it past her
to bribe a judge.

14:16.522 --> 14:19.150
I'll try to get a warrant
to search his financial records.

14:19.150 --> 14:21.486
Be careful.
Judges look after each other.

14:21.486 --> 14:23.112
You have to approach
someone you trust.

14:23.112 --> 14:24.697
Judge Zuckerman and I
go way back.

14:24.697 --> 14:26.115
She will not warn Rivas.

14:26.115 --> 14:28.117
But will she openly
go against another judge?

14:28.117 --> 14:29.285
There's only one way
to find out.

14:29.285 --> 14:31.704
If Rivas is corrupt,

14:31.704 --> 14:35.208
it calls all his cases
into question.

14:35.208 --> 14:37.502
Even the ones
he didn't throw.

14:37.502 --> 14:39.670
No telling how many criminals
could go free.

14:39.670 --> 14:41.506
I know.

14:41.506 --> 14:43.424
Keep me posted.

14:43.424 --> 14:46.135
Lucy:
How much do you spend on food?

14:46.135 --> 14:48.221
I'm not sure,
but I think I still have

14:48.221 --> 14:50.098
all my takeout receipts.

14:50.098 --> 14:52.934
Okay.
How much do you order in?

14:52.934 --> 14:54.894
You know, I feel like
there's a right answer,

14:54.894 --> 14:56.395
but I don't have an idea
what it is.

14:56.395 --> 14:58.648
Cooking is a lot more
cost-effective, but --

14:58.648 --> 14:59.899
You do know
how to cook, right?

14:59.899 --> 15:01.609
Oh, yeah.
I make the perfect martini.

15:01.609 --> 15:03.236
Lopez: You were right
about Sonia Laetner.

15:03.236 --> 15:04.570
She wasn't on
any flight manifest,

15:04.570 --> 15:06.781
and none of her family in Ohio
has heard from her.

15:06.781 --> 15:08.116
What about her cellphone?

15:08.116 --> 15:09.909
It last pinged near their house,
then went dead.

15:09.909 --> 15:12.120
We're gonna find her body
in Griffith Park, aren't we?

15:12.120 --> 15:14.956
Bring her husband in.
I want to talk to him.
Okay.

15:14.956 --> 15:17.708
♪ This is your gunpoint
confession ♪

15:17.708 --> 15:19.127
[ Target pops up,
paintball gun fires ]

15:19.127 --> 15:22.505
[ Heavy metal music playing ]

15:22.505 --> 15:24.382
Mad Dog: [ Through headset ]
<i>There's no excuses</i>
<i>for a bad shot.</i>

15:24.382 --> 15:26.050
<i>Metro never misses.</i>

15:26.050 --> 15:30.304
♪♪

15:30.304 --> 15:34.183
♪ A serpent tongue,
a jealous type ♪

15:34.183 --> 15:36.394
<i>Good call.</i>
<i>Mikey's a lovely man.</i>

15:36.394 --> 15:39.021
<i>Although his ex-wife</i>
<i>might disagree.</i>

15:39.021 --> 15:40.731
[ Target pops up ]

15:40.731 --> 15:44.402
♪ Leeching hope
from the ones you know ♪

15:44.402 --> 15:48.322
♪ I will not leave you whole ♪

15:48.322 --> 15:49.949
[ Alarm blares, bell rings ]

15:49.949 --> 15:51.701
<i>Yeah, Bradford. Nice.</i>

15:54.495 --> 15:57.415
[ Applause ]

16:00.126 --> 16:02.670
Mad Dog: Well, clearly
you got the goods to be here.

16:02.670 --> 16:06.257
And now that you're one of us,
you get the company ink.

16:06.257 --> 16:07.967
What are you talking about?
What ink?

16:07.967 --> 16:10.678
It's the tattoo
we all have, brother.

16:10.678 --> 16:12.138
It's how we
show our loyalty.

16:12.138 --> 16:13.556
Oh, come on.
We all know

16:13.556 --> 16:15.349
that as soon as a group of cops
get the same tattoo,

16:15.349 --> 16:17.101
they're going to prison.

16:17.101 --> 16:18.853
What are you
trying to say?

16:18.853 --> 16:21.355
♪♪

16:21.355 --> 16:23.191
Alright, let me see it.

16:23.191 --> 16:26.611
♪♪

16:26.611 --> 16:30.031
[ Laughs ]

16:30.031 --> 16:31.449
Lighten up, brother.
Here.

16:31.449 --> 16:33.034
Here.

16:33.034 --> 16:34.076
Have a unicorn.

16:34.076 --> 16:35.578
Too kind.
[ Laughs ]

16:35.578 --> 16:37.246
Too kind. Thank you.

16:37.246 --> 16:39.707
♪♪

16:39.707 --> 16:42.585
They're testing you,
seeing how far you'll bend.

16:42.585 --> 16:43.794
Yeah, I saw
the same kind of thing

16:43.794 --> 16:45.463
when I was
in the military.

16:45.463 --> 16:48.216
Not about how many stripes
on your sleeves with this crew.

16:48.216 --> 16:50.509
It's all good.
Team building.

16:50.509 --> 16:54.263
If you're gonna lead this team,
they need to know who you are.

16:54.263 --> 16:57.225
Show them the Tim Bradford
that was tapped to join Metro

16:57.225 --> 16:58.851
in the first place.

17:01.229 --> 17:02.480
Thanks.

17:04.565 --> 17:07.401
Lopez: Mr. Laetner,
if your wife, Sonia, is in Ohio,

17:07.401 --> 17:10.529
do you have any idea why
her car was parked in Hollywood

17:10.529 --> 17:13.574
with her phone and purse
still inside?

17:13.574 --> 17:15.451
Deon: I don't know.

17:15.451 --> 17:17.286
See, in my line of work,

17:17.286 --> 17:20.122
when a woman takes a last-minute
trip with no money,

17:20.122 --> 17:22.583
9 times out of 10, her husband's
got something to do with it.

17:22.583 --> 17:23.709
So where's Sonia?

17:23.709 --> 17:25.544
I don't know.

17:25.544 --> 17:27.546
I swear.
That's the truth.

17:27.546 --> 17:28.881
Look, you're right.

17:28.881 --> 17:31.092
I-I did lie
to your officers earlier.

17:31.092 --> 17:33.928
But he said if I involved
the police, he'd kill Sonia.

17:33.928 --> 17:37.682
Who said that?
The man who took her.

17:37.682 --> 17:40.059
Look, Sonia never
came home last night.

17:40.059 --> 17:42.562
I was about to call the police
when my phone rang,

17:42.562 --> 17:44.689
and they said if I ever wanted
to see her again,

17:44.689 --> 17:46.691
I'd have to pay him
$250,000.

17:46.691 --> 17:47.733
I need the number.

17:47.733 --> 17:50.319
It said "blocked."

17:50.319 --> 17:52.947
Listen. I know
I-I shouldn't have lied,

17:52.947 --> 17:54.991
but I'd really prefer
to handle this myself.

17:54.991 --> 17:56.951
Unfortunately, that's no longer
an option, Mr. Laetner.

17:56.951 --> 17:58.703
And you owe it to your wife

17:58.703 --> 18:00.955
to use every resource available
to bring her home safely.

18:00.955 --> 18:02.123
What do you think
I've been trying to do?!

18:06.711 --> 18:08.379
You're right.
I-I'm -- I'm sorry.

18:08.379 --> 18:11.632
It's alright.
It's a stressful situation.

18:11.632 --> 18:14.343
Now, what can you tell me
about the man's voice?

18:14.343 --> 18:15.636
To the left.
[ <i>Video game beeping</i> ]

18:15.636 --> 18:17.847
To the left.
To the right.

18:17.847 --> 18:19.265
To the left.
Oh! Watch out!

18:19.265 --> 18:21.225
Mm.
[ <i>Explosion, beeping stops</i> ]

18:21.225 --> 18:24.228
I thought you were gonna
get first place.

18:24.228 --> 18:26.188
You don't want
to play again?

18:29.233 --> 18:31.068
You know,
I don't like to brag,

18:31.068 --> 18:34.196
but I'm, like, really good
friends with the cops here.

18:36.449 --> 18:37.617
They're doing
everything they can

18:37.617 --> 18:40.453
to make sure
your mom comes home to you.

18:40.453 --> 18:43.706
And until she does,
you can call me.

18:43.706 --> 18:45.541
Whenever you want.

18:45.541 --> 18:47.543
Even if it's just to talk.

18:47.543 --> 18:48.753
Got it?

18:48.753 --> 18:50.046
[ Footsteps approaching ]

18:50.921 --> 18:52.965
Cosmo, let's go.

18:58.429 --> 19:00.056
He did not look happy.

19:00.056 --> 19:01.724
Lopez: He's not.
What happened?

19:01.724 --> 19:03.225
Claims Sonia was kidnapped
for a ransom

19:03.225 --> 19:04.810
but doesn't want
the cops involved.

19:04.810 --> 19:07.146
Do we buy that?
He's already lied to us once.

19:07.146 --> 19:09.398
I'm not taking anything
at face value.

19:09.398 --> 19:11.067
You spend a lot of time
at the house.

19:11.067 --> 19:12.234
Do you think he'd hurt her?

19:12.234 --> 19:14.445
No. He's --
He's never been violent.

19:14.445 --> 19:17.323
I've heard them argue
maybe like twice.

19:17.323 --> 19:19.075
Why?
Do you think he killed her?

19:21.494 --> 19:23.663
I'm not ruling anything out.

19:23.663 --> 19:25.247
We need a team
to search the house.

19:25.247 --> 19:26.832
Once they're done,
I want units parked outside.

19:26.832 --> 19:28.209
If he leaves
for any reason,

19:28.209 --> 19:29.919
I want him followed.
You got it.

19:29.919 --> 19:32.004
I'm gonna get a warrant for
his phone. For whatever reason,

19:32.004 --> 19:34.006
he cannot be allowed
to make a money drop alone --

19:34.006 --> 19:36.008
if there even is
a money drop.

19:36.967 --> 19:39.303
Alright. Come on.

19:39.303 --> 19:41.305
[ Siren wailing ]

19:49.355 --> 19:51.273
Nolan: Detectives just
got a partial plate

19:51.273 --> 19:53.317
<i>from the surveillance footage</i>
<i>near the ambulance shooting.</i>

19:53.317 --> 19:56.862
Shooter left driving
a 1992 red Sentra.

19:56.862 --> 19:58.239
What do you got here?

19:58.239 --> 20:00.241
New car fire.
No obvious sign of arson,

20:00.241 --> 20:01.742
but that's for the investigators
to decide.

20:01.742 --> 20:03.536
Let's call in an 11-85

20:03.536 --> 20:05.705
for impound to our location.
Copy that.

20:05.705 --> 20:07.289
So any news on that shooting
from this morning?

20:07.289 --> 20:08.916
It's got all my guys
a little on edge.

20:08.916 --> 20:11.043
Yeah. We got a lot of good
detectives working on that.

20:11.043 --> 20:12.503
We'll let you know
as soon as we learn something.

20:12.503 --> 20:14.380
Appreciate it.
Tow truck's 30 minutes out.

20:14.380 --> 20:15.631
Nolan: Right.
[ Gunshots ]

20:15.631 --> 20:17.007
Get down. Get down.

20:17.007 --> 20:19.176
[ Gunshots continue ]

20:19.176 --> 20:21.011
Pull him up.

20:21.011 --> 20:22.930
We got you. We got help coming.
Call it in.

20:22.930 --> 20:24.640
Control, shots fired
at our location.

20:24.640 --> 20:26.434
We have a firefighter down.
He is conscious and breathing.

20:26.434 --> 20:28.144
Send an R. A. and backup.

20:28.144 --> 20:30.312
[ Engine revving,
tires screeching ]

20:30.312 --> 20:32.231
[ People shouting indistinctly ]

20:32.231 --> 20:33.482
Control,
also send an airship.

20:33.482 --> 20:36.694
Suspect fleeing location,
red sedan, east on Olympic.

20:42.158 --> 20:45.244
Captain Burke: [ Through phone ]
<i>We answer more than</i>
<i>1,000 calls a day.</i>

20:45.244 --> 20:46.495
<i>My people can't do their jobs</i>

20:46.495 --> 20:47.496
<i>with a bullseye</i>
<i>on their backs.</i>

20:47.496 --> 20:49.331
Effective immediately,
the LAPD will dispatch units

20:49.331 --> 20:52.042
to accompany
your firefighters on calls.

20:52.042 --> 20:54.462
<i>We had cops at the</i>
<i>burned-out car. Didn't help.</i>

20:54.462 --> 20:56.589
<i>You need to</i>
<i>catch this guy now!</i>

20:56.589 --> 20:59.008
[ Click, dial tone ]
Yeah.

20:59.008 --> 21:00.468
[ Knock on glass ]

21:00.468 --> 21:02.970
You wanted to see me, sir?

21:02.970 --> 21:05.181
Yes.
Your mother called.

21:05.181 --> 21:07.600
Sir?
As in me.

21:07.600 --> 21:10.728
As in asking why
her son is dodging her calls.

21:10.728 --> 21:13.397
She even called Dispatch.

21:13.397 --> 21:15.483
I am so sorry.

21:15.483 --> 21:17.610
Save your apologies.

21:17.610 --> 21:20.196
I don't want to hear
from your crazy mother again.

21:20.196 --> 21:21.989
I'll get -- If you --
I'll --

21:21.989 --> 21:23.282
Go.

21:23.282 --> 21:26.035
♪♪

21:28.746 --> 21:30.206
Nolan: You okay?

21:30.206 --> 21:31.999
I'll be better
once there's not some psycho

21:31.999 --> 21:33.626
gunning for every fire crew
in the city.

21:33.626 --> 21:35.377
We'll find him.

21:35.377 --> 21:37.046
It's only a matter of time.
[ Cellphone ringing ]

21:37.046 --> 21:39.131
Yeah.

21:39.131 --> 21:41.425
Mom?
Well, it's from
a different number.

21:41.425 --> 21:43.052
Hello.
Dr. Schnitzel:
<i>Hello. I'm Dr. Schnitzel.</i>

21:43.052 --> 21:44.595
<i>Your mother was just admitted,</i>

21:44.595 --> 21:46.347
<i>and we need to verify</i>
<i>her insurance.</i>

21:46.347 --> 21:47.890
Really? Dr. Schnitzel?

21:47.890 --> 21:49.934
You -- You -- You really think
I'm gonna buy that?

21:49.934 --> 21:52.144
<i>I don't --</i>
Look. You tell my mom

21:52.144 --> 21:53.771
it's not happening.

21:53.771 --> 21:55.356
Alright?
A-And word of advice --

21:55.356 --> 21:57.942
Don't let her pull you
into any of her schemes.

21:57.942 --> 21:59.777
What was that?
Ah, vintage Mom.

21:59.777 --> 22:01.570
She's moved on to number 5
in her playbook --

22:01.570 --> 22:03.030
pretend to be sick
for sympathy,

22:03.030 --> 22:05.241
get me to give my credit card
number to an accomplice.

22:07.618 --> 22:09.286
Cosmo would love this.

22:09.286 --> 22:11.705
I've never seen a kid
who was such a health nut.

22:11.705 --> 22:13.249
[ Chuckles ]

22:13.249 --> 22:16.252
You've been putting in
a lot of hours at their house.

22:16.252 --> 22:17.586
Not that many.

22:17.586 --> 22:20.089
And you're working
the night shift somewhere.

22:20.089 --> 22:23.300
This morning, you were
<i>not</i> coming home from a party.

22:23.300 --> 22:25.970
Not dressed like that.
You were coming home from a job.

22:25.970 --> 22:27.221
What's going on with you?

22:27.221 --> 22:28.430
You need money
or something?

22:28.430 --> 22:30.641
♪ I'd just play along ♪

22:30.641 --> 22:33.227
I got to get
that first month, last month,

22:33.227 --> 22:35.396
and security deposit.

22:35.396 --> 22:37.439
♪ Now you're leaving ♪

22:37.439 --> 22:40.192
It's not like
I can stay here forever.

22:40.192 --> 22:42.403
Why would you say that?
Of course you can.

22:42.403 --> 22:43.821
How's that gonna work?

22:43.821 --> 22:45.573
You, me, and Tim?

22:45.573 --> 22:48.784
And that's assuming you wouldn't
want to get your own place.

22:48.784 --> 22:50.828
Either way,
there's no room for me.

22:50.828 --> 22:53.080
[ Door opens ]

22:53.080 --> 22:55.332
Hey. Sorry I'm late.

22:55.332 --> 22:56.709
Ready for the movie?
I found out

22:56.709 --> 22:58.460
that "Time After Time"
is on a streaming platform.

23:00.045 --> 23:03.090
I think I'm gonna crash.

23:03.090 --> 23:05.759
Are you sure?
David Warner is amazing in this.

23:05.759 --> 23:09.889
♪ Before I started ♪

23:09.889 --> 23:13.309
[ Door shuts ]
Well, I guess it's just us.

23:13.309 --> 23:15.352
Popcorn?
Yeah, sure.

23:17.354 --> 23:19.189
Any chance your judge signed off
on the warrant?

23:19.189 --> 23:22.026
Uh, short answer, no.
"Insufficient probable cause."

23:22.026 --> 23:23.736
No judge wants to imply

23:23.736 --> 23:25.738
that a fellow member of the
bench is guilty of malfeasance.

23:25.738 --> 23:27.489
Well, no warrant,
no evidence.

23:27.489 --> 23:30.200
No way of proving
your judge is bent.

23:30.200 --> 23:31.577
I'm having a hard time
believing it myself.

23:31.577 --> 23:33.329
He's one of the most
honorable people I know.

23:33.329 --> 23:35.247
Yeah, I guess no one
is incorruptible.

23:35.247 --> 23:37.666
[ Sighs ]

23:37.666 --> 23:40.461
You know, his chambers
are just a few doors down.

23:40.461 --> 23:42.171
What if I go talk to him?

23:42.171 --> 23:44.423
I've been where he is.
Maybe he'll open up.

23:44.423 --> 23:46.759
I don't have
any better ideas.

23:48.552 --> 23:50.721
I got to go.

23:50.721 --> 23:52.514
Wesley.

23:52.514 --> 23:53.682
You're working late.

23:53.682 --> 23:55.684
Yeah, you, too.
Just chatting with Rivas?

23:55.684 --> 23:58.354
Reminiscing.
You know, a lot's changed.

23:58.354 --> 24:00.898
We split up.
You got all sanctimonious.

24:00.898 --> 24:02.107
You sold your soul
to the devil.

24:02.107 --> 24:03.651
[ Both scoff ]

24:03.651 --> 24:06.153
It's really that simple to you,
isn't it?

24:06.153 --> 24:07.237
Good and evil.

24:07.237 --> 24:09.365
In this case, yeah.

24:09.365 --> 24:10.783
It is.

24:10.783 --> 24:13.911
See you in court.
Hmm.

24:13.911 --> 24:15.329
[ Elevator bell dings ]

24:15.329 --> 24:16.956
[ Sighs ]

24:19.833 --> 24:20.709
[ Knock on door ]

24:20.709 --> 24:24.129
[ Door opens ]

24:24.129 --> 24:26.548
Oh, Mr. Evers.
[ Door closes ]

24:26.548 --> 24:28.217
I'm afraid
I was just leaving.

24:28.217 --> 24:29.718
I'll be brief.

24:29.718 --> 24:31.720
I know you're
throwing cases.

24:31.720 --> 24:33.931
I beg your pardon?

24:33.931 --> 24:36.100
I don't have any evidence.

24:36.100 --> 24:38.185
Monica's too smart for that.

24:38.185 --> 24:40.062
Elijah Stone
is too smart for that.

24:42.856 --> 24:44.942
You didn't know, did you?

24:44.942 --> 24:46.777
He is her biggest client.

24:46.777 --> 24:48.779
Every time she asks you
to rule in her favor,

24:48.779 --> 24:50.280
it's for one of his guys.

24:50.280 --> 24:52.658
You're helping
rebuild his empire.

24:52.658 --> 24:55.035
I'm helping? The whole reason
he's back on the streets

24:55.035 --> 24:56.954
is because of you!
I know!

24:56.954 --> 24:58.872
I am well aware
of my part in all this.

24:58.872 --> 25:00.916
Which is why I know that
you haven't slept in months,

25:00.916 --> 25:02.251
you can't concentrate,

25:02.251 --> 25:03.711
and sometimes your heart
races so fast,

25:03.711 --> 25:05.129
you think you're having
a heart attack.

25:05.129 --> 25:07.881
A life lived
in the service of justice.

25:07.881 --> 25:09.800
I always wanted that
to be my legacy.

25:09.800 --> 25:12.428
It still can be.

25:12.428 --> 25:14.138
Help me put Elijah
where he belongs.

25:14.138 --> 25:16.557
He goes after
anyone who crosses him.

25:16.557 --> 25:18.851
I'm sure you could cut a deal
for witness protection.

25:20.686 --> 25:23.689
And I'm sure I have no idea
what you're talking about.

25:23.689 --> 25:25.315
Please leave.

25:27.484 --> 25:29.987
You know how to reach me
if you change your mind.

25:29.987 --> 25:36.577
♪♪

25:36.577 --> 25:42.916
♪♪

25:47.087 --> 25:49.673
Hey.
Any updates on Cosmo's mom?

25:49.673 --> 25:52.092
Uh, no. We had units
parked outside all night.

25:52.092 --> 25:53.260
There was no movement.

25:53.260 --> 25:55.471
But, you know, they have
his phones tapped,

25:55.471 --> 25:57.431
so if the kidnappers call,
we'll know.

25:57.431 --> 25:59.850
Do you think
she's still alive?

25:59.850 --> 26:02.352
Listen.
If it's about money,

26:02.352 --> 26:04.229
they have every incentive
to keep her alive

26:04.229 --> 26:05.147
until they get
what they want.

26:05.147 --> 26:07.149
[ Cellphone ringing ]

26:09.443 --> 26:11.612
Cosmo?
Cosmo: <i>Dad says</i>
<i>I'm not going to school,</i>

26:11.612 --> 26:13.363
<i>and he won't</i>
<i>come out of his office.</i>

26:13.363 --> 26:14.740
<i>Can you come over?</i>

26:14.740 --> 26:16.742
I'll be right there.

26:16.742 --> 26:18.786
Hey. I don't think
that's a good idea.

26:18.786 --> 26:21.955
I have to.

26:21.955 --> 26:25.084
Tamara? Um, I'll be
parked outside, okay?

26:27.795 --> 26:29.254
You got here early.

26:29.254 --> 26:32.091
I did.
I had a thought this morning.

26:32.091 --> 26:35.219
Our shooter is specifically
targeting firefighters.

26:35.219 --> 26:36.470
You don't just
get up one morning

26:36.470 --> 26:39.348
and decide to start
shooting at LAFD.

26:39.348 --> 26:41.100
This is what
it escalated to.

26:41.100 --> 26:42.684
Okay, so you thought
it may have started somewhere.

26:42.684 --> 26:44.353
Exactly. So I started
looking into

26:44.353 --> 26:46.230
any case that involves
the fire department --

26:46.230 --> 26:47.981
complaints, lawsuits,
patrol calls --

26:47.981 --> 26:49.108
anything and everything.

26:49.108 --> 26:50.317
I can help.

26:50.317 --> 26:51.693
No need.

26:51.693 --> 26:53.529
I got him.

26:53.529 --> 26:56.323
His name is Anthony Pickett.
He's a firefighter --

26:56.323 --> 26:58.408
ex-firefighter,
to be specific.

26:58.408 --> 26:59.952
Got cut
and didn't take it well?

26:59.952 --> 27:01.245
Yeah, he made it
through the academy

27:01.245 --> 27:02.704
but washed out
during probation.

27:02.704 --> 27:05.249
Other firefighters found him
to be difficult and aggressive.

27:05.249 --> 27:08.460
He actually picked a fight with
an old-timer who later found

27:08.460 --> 27:10.754
the hose had been cut
on his breathing apparatus.

27:10.754 --> 27:13.257
Mm. Short fuse.

27:13.257 --> 27:15.634
Few days after that, he showed
up at the station that cut him

27:15.634 --> 27:17.719
looking to get his job back.

27:17.719 --> 27:21.056
Unit was called out, but
he seemed to accept his fate.

27:21.056 --> 27:22.641
But apparently,
he couldn't let it go.

27:22.641 --> 27:24.017
Okay,
how do we know it's him?

27:24.017 --> 27:25.477
Cross-referenced
his registered vehicle

27:25.477 --> 27:27.646
with our description
and partial plate.

27:27.646 --> 27:29.189
It's a match.
I already put out a BOLO.

27:29.189 --> 27:30.858
I'll send units
to sit on the house.

27:30.858 --> 27:32.234
Maybe we'll get lucky.

27:32.234 --> 27:34.528
Good work.

27:34.528 --> 27:36.238
Lucy: Thank you.
I know I volunteered us

27:36.238 --> 27:38.198
for the most boring
detail ever.

27:38.198 --> 27:39.700
Of course.
You're worried about Tamara.

27:39.700 --> 27:40.868
I get it.
Yeah.

27:40.868 --> 27:42.411
Plus, it gives me time
to apartment-hunt.

27:42.411 --> 27:43.787
Mm.

27:43.787 --> 27:45.455
It's hard to find a place
with a pool.

27:45.455 --> 27:47.124
♪♪

27:47.124 --> 27:48.500
Yeah. I mean,
you might need

27:48.500 --> 27:50.377
to be a little flexible
with that one.

27:50.377 --> 27:53.380
Well, I used your "rent should
be 30% of your salary" rule...

27:53.380 --> 27:55.716
Oh.
...and -- and there's like
nothing in my price range.

27:55.716 --> 27:57.175
Well...

27:57.175 --> 27:59.052
hold on.
That place is cute.

27:59.052 --> 28:01.013
Yeah.
This place is trash.

28:01.013 --> 28:03.223
Uh, that place
looks like my apartment.

28:06.018 --> 28:09.563
[ <i>Video game beeping</i> ]

28:09.563 --> 28:10.939
[ Door opens ]

28:10.939 --> 28:14.526
[ Door shuts ]

28:14.526 --> 28:16.904
I'm gonna go
check on your dad.

28:16.904 --> 28:18.989
[ <i>Beeping continues</i> ]

28:18.989 --> 28:20.782
Deon: [ Muffled ]
No. You listen to me.

28:20.782 --> 28:23.744
If you do anything to hurt her,
I swear --

28:23.744 --> 28:25.412
That's not possible.

28:25.412 --> 28:28.290
You're not giving me
enough time. I need more time.

28:28.290 --> 28:30.667
I can't!

28:30.667 --> 28:33.795
No. She's got
nothing to do with this.

28:33.795 --> 28:35.047
And how do I know that?

28:35.047 --> 28:37.132
[ Cellphone clicks ]
Please...

28:37.132 --> 28:38.884
let me talk to her.
Put her on.

28:38.884 --> 28:40.969
[ Cellphone rings, clicks ]

28:40.969 --> 28:42.721
Hey.
I think Deon's on the phone

28:42.721 --> 28:44.056
with the kidnappers now.
I don't have your money!

28:44.056 --> 28:45.307
I can hear him shouting.

28:45.307 --> 28:47.225
What's he saying?
<i>I can't make it out.</i>

28:47.225 --> 28:48.518
He's emotional.

28:48.518 --> 28:49.937
[ Muffled ]
I'm sorry. Please put her on.

28:49.937 --> 28:51.271
It has to be them.
Please.

28:51.271 --> 28:52.981
Tamara, the detectives
are listening

28:52.981 --> 28:55.233
to all of his known phones,
okay? He's under surveillance.

28:55.233 --> 28:57.527
Just let the investigators
do their job.

28:57.527 --> 28:59.905
All you got to do is make sure
that kid is safe. That's it.

28:59.905 --> 29:01.740
His known phones.

29:01.740 --> 29:02.741
What if he's on a burner?

29:02.741 --> 29:04.242
Tamara...

29:04.242 --> 29:06.787
[ Muffled ] No. She's got
nothing to do with this!

29:06.787 --> 29:09.665
How do I know that? Huh?

29:09.665 --> 29:13.168
Please...let me talk to her.
Put her on.

29:13.168 --> 29:15.545
He's saying, "Let me
talk to her. Put her on."

29:18.382 --> 29:20.592
<i>"I don't have your money.</i>
<i>I spent it."</i>

29:20.592 --> 29:24.304
...think you'd miss it.
"I didn't think you'd miss it."

29:24.304 --> 29:25.847
I'm sorry.
"I'm sorry."

29:25.847 --> 29:26.807
Please. Don't hurt her.

29:26.807 --> 29:29.351
"Please don't hurt her."

29:29.351 --> 29:33.105
Uh, Tamara, don't let him know
that you heard him, okay?

29:33.105 --> 29:36.149
Just get as far away as you can.
We're heading in right now.

29:36.149 --> 29:38.777
That bastard.
This happened because of him.

29:38.777 --> 29:41.363
[ Muffled click ]

29:41.363 --> 29:43.490
He hung up.
I got to go.

29:43.490 --> 29:46.535
♪♪

29:46.535 --> 29:48.787
What are you doing?
Listening in?

29:48.787 --> 29:50.747
Yeah.
I heard everything.

29:50.747 --> 29:52.040
You did this for money?

29:52.040 --> 29:53.125
You don't understand.

29:53.125 --> 29:55.627
You're right.
I don't understand.

29:55.627 --> 29:57.546
Police are on their way.

29:57.546 --> 29:59.756
Let them help you.
No. These guys will kill her!

29:59.756 --> 30:00.757
[ Banging on door ]

30:00.757 --> 30:01.758
Aaron: [ Muffled ]
Police!

30:01.758 --> 30:03.051
[ Door opens ]

30:03.051 --> 30:04.678
Mr. Laetner, you need
to come with us.

30:10.308 --> 30:12.811
Time to come clean. Which one of
your clients did you steal from?

30:12.811 --> 30:14.271
Are you sure Cosmo's okay?

30:14.271 --> 30:15.856
Tamara is with him.
He's fine.

30:15.856 --> 30:17.024
You need to focus.

30:17.024 --> 30:18.400
We know you were
skimming money,

30:18.400 --> 30:20.110
and we know someone took
your wife in retaliation.

30:20.110 --> 30:21.945
Who was it?

30:21.945 --> 30:23.697
Reed Butler.

30:23.697 --> 30:25.657
That wasn't very smart.
He's killed for a lot less.

30:25.657 --> 30:28.035
I know.
But I figured he's a criminal.

30:28.035 --> 30:30.120
I'm stealing back
the money he stole.

30:30.120 --> 30:31.705
It's justice, kind of.

30:31.705 --> 30:33.206
How noble of you.

30:33.206 --> 30:35.834
Look, I know I'm not innocent
in all this,

30:35.834 --> 30:37.794
but my wife is.

30:37.794 --> 30:39.463
Please help.

30:39.463 --> 30:41.214
I need you to call
the people who have your wife

30:41.214 --> 30:42.299
and tell them
you've got the money.

30:42.299 --> 30:43.759
Set up a place
for the exchange.

30:43.759 --> 30:45.927
He knows I don't have the money.
He'll know I'm lying.

30:45.927 --> 30:47.304
Tell them a family member
came through,

30:47.304 --> 30:48.680
wired it to you
this morning.

30:48.680 --> 30:51.224
Okay. A-And then?

30:51.224 --> 30:52.559
Then you're gonna
write down a confession

30:52.559 --> 30:55.062
detailing how you embezzled
money from a client.

30:57.230 --> 30:58.732
I'm going to jail,
aren't I?

30:58.732 --> 31:02.027
Probably.

31:02.027 --> 31:03.737
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm such an idiot.

31:03.737 --> 31:05.947
No argument
from this side of the table.

31:05.947 --> 31:07.699
Rivas texted
early this morning.

31:07.699 --> 31:09.326
Was it a full
admission of guilt?

31:09.326 --> 31:11.244
"Can we talk?" He's been careful
not to admit anything,

31:11.244 --> 31:12.537
but I can tell he wants to.

31:12.537 --> 31:14.331
[ Sighs ]

31:15.707 --> 31:16.917
Judge Rivas?

31:22.422 --> 31:28.720
♪♪

31:28.720 --> 31:31.389
He's cold.

31:31.389 --> 31:33.809
It looks like there's
no injury, no blood.

31:33.809 --> 31:35.310
It looks like
maybe a heart attack.

31:35.310 --> 31:36.812
Elijah did this.

31:36.812 --> 31:38.772
We don't know that for sure.
At his age --

31:38.772 --> 31:40.107
But Monica
saw me last night.

31:40.107 --> 31:43.944
She knew I could
get through to him.

31:43.944 --> 31:47.656
Elijah had him killed
to protect her.

31:47.656 --> 31:50.659
♪♪

31:50.659 --> 31:54.079
♪ No definition ♪

31:54.079 --> 31:57.541
♪♪

31:57.541 --> 32:01.002
♪ Not empathy ♪

32:01.002 --> 32:02.879
Tim: Alright, everyone
switch to channel 9.

32:02.879 --> 32:04.673
Listen up. We have
a confirmed hostage situation

32:04.673 --> 32:07.134
at that compound
across the street.

32:07.134 --> 32:09.511
Hostage is Sonia Laetner.
White female, dark hair.

32:09.511 --> 32:11.263
Last seen with an orange sweater
and black pants.

32:11.263 --> 32:12.722
We've identified
five suspects on site,

32:12.722 --> 32:14.641
but there could be more.

32:14.641 --> 32:16.184
We don't know which building
our hostage is being held in,

32:16.184 --> 32:17.394
so we need to clear everything.

32:17.394 --> 32:19.187
Detective Lopez
will be our spotter.

32:19.187 --> 32:20.438
She'll provide overwatch.

32:20.438 --> 32:22.566
Why not let Metro
provide overwatch?

32:22.566 --> 32:24.442
Because we need
all our boots on the ground.

32:24.442 --> 32:28.113
And there's no one I'd rather
have on my six than <i>La Adelita.</i>

32:28.113 --> 32:29.322
Oh.

32:29.322 --> 32:32.409
I'm sorry, ma'am.
I-I had no idea.

32:32.409 --> 32:34.035
You're a legend
at the range.

32:34.035 --> 32:35.912
No worries.
Go get her back.

32:35.912 --> 32:37.747
You heard her.
Let's move.

32:37.747 --> 32:39.374
No mistakes.

32:39.374 --> 32:45.797
♪♪

32:47.257 --> 32:56.892
♪♪

32:56.892 --> 33:06.610
♪♪

33:06.610 --> 33:16.453
♪♪

33:16.453 --> 33:18.580
In position.
Are we clear?

33:18.580 --> 33:24.252
♪♪

33:24.252 --> 33:26.463
Main concourse is clear.
Green and go.

33:26.463 --> 33:36.264
♪♪

33:36.264 --> 33:46.399
♪♪

33:46.399 --> 33:48.693
[ Through speakers ] ♪ <i>Money in</i>
<i>the mattress, pull up stunt ♪</i>

33:48.693 --> 33:50.820
♪ <i>Running to the money</i>
<i>like my last name Gump</i> ♪

33:50.820 --> 33:53.657
♪ <i>Got a briefcase in the trunk,</i>
<i>hell nah I ain't no punk</i> ♪

33:53.657 --> 33:55.200
♪ <i>I do what I want</i>
<i>not what you say</i> ♪

33:55.200 --> 34:04.125
♪♪

34:04.125 --> 34:13.093
♪♪

34:13.093 --> 34:15.553
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

34:15.553 --> 34:16.930
[ Whispering ]
Cover me.

34:16.930 --> 34:22.560
♪♪

34:22.560 --> 34:24.271
[ Indistinct conversation ]

34:24.271 --> 34:25.897
[ Stones clattering ]

34:25.897 --> 34:27.482
Police!
Drop the weapon!

34:27.482 --> 34:28.942
Step away from the weapon.
Put your hands up.

34:28.942 --> 34:31.111
Hand up. Turn around.

34:31.111 --> 34:32.487
Put your hands on your head.

34:32.487 --> 34:35.782
♪♪

34:35.782 --> 34:36.908
Hands behind your back.

34:36.908 --> 34:38.493
B Team, two in custody.

34:38.493 --> 34:46.584
♪♪

34:46.584 --> 34:54.926
♪♪

34:54.926 --> 34:57.762
Adam Team, I need trailers
for one in custody. Ramp room.

34:57.762 --> 34:59.222
Moving forward on our sweep.

35:01.266 --> 35:02.809
♪ <i>It's how I envisioned it</i> ♪

35:02.809 --> 35:04.811
♪ <i>I make it rain</i>
<i>and she go ham</i> ♪

35:04.811 --> 35:06.646
♪ <i>Girl pop it for the gram</i>
<i>make me wanna</i> ♪

35:06.646 --> 35:07.814
[ Loud bang ]

35:07.814 --> 35:09.816
Mad Dog: Freeze! Police!

35:09.816 --> 35:11.943
Get on the ground!
Don't move! Don't move!

35:11.943 --> 35:14.863
<i>The ground! Now!</i>

35:14.863 --> 35:16.573
C Team, two in custody.

35:16.573 --> 35:22.579
♪♪

35:22.579 --> 35:29.044
♪♪

35:29.044 --> 35:32.756
[ Sonia sobbing ]
Swan: Shut up already!

35:32.756 --> 35:34.507
I said shut up!

35:34.507 --> 35:38.345
♪♪

35:38.345 --> 35:40.305
Kill the power
when I give the signal.

35:40.305 --> 35:48.146
♪♪

35:48.146 --> 35:49.856
It is what it is.

35:49.856 --> 35:51.775
Crying about it
ain't gonna do no good.

35:51.775 --> 35:55.737
♪♪

35:55.737 --> 35:57.113
[ Sobs ]

35:57.113 --> 35:59.824
♪♪

35:59.824 --> 36:01.868
[ Phone line ringing ]

36:01.868 --> 36:03.411
♪♪

36:03.411 --> 36:06.539
Tim: [ Quietly ]
Come on. Just take one step.

36:06.539 --> 36:08.249
[ Ringing continues ]

36:08.249 --> 36:10.835
Something's wrong.
Time's up.

36:10.835 --> 36:12.712
[ Gunshot, Sonia screams ]

36:15.632 --> 36:17.634
[ Sobbing ]

36:17.634 --> 36:21.304
♪♪

36:21.304 --> 36:22.847
Tim: It's okay.

36:22.847 --> 36:25.016
♪♪

36:25.016 --> 36:26.226
Adam Team, one in custody.

36:26.226 --> 36:29.104
Hostage is safe.
We are Code 4.

36:29.104 --> 36:30.438
It's okay.

36:30.438 --> 36:31.898
It's okay. You're safe now.

36:36.111 --> 36:39.280
[ <i>Mid-tempo music playing</i>
<i>on car radio</i> ]

36:39.280 --> 36:41.449
7-Adam-15,
eyes on suspect.

36:41.449 --> 36:51.418
♪♪

36:51.418 --> 36:53.211
[ Car door opens ]

36:53.211 --> 36:59.426
♪♪

36:59.426 --> 37:05.724
♪♪

37:05.724 --> 37:08.601
Nolan: Police!

37:08.601 --> 37:09.686
Don't.

37:09.686 --> 37:10.937
You move an inch
towards that trunk,

37:10.937 --> 37:13.106
I'll be forced to shoot you.

37:13.106 --> 37:14.774
<i>Hands in the air.</i>

37:14.774 --> 37:16.401
<i>Now!</i>

37:16.401 --> 37:18.319
Okay.

37:18.319 --> 37:20.572
Step back
towards my voice.

37:20.572 --> 37:22.866
Again. Again.

37:22.866 --> 37:24.743
On your knees.

37:24.743 --> 37:31.791
♪♪

37:31.791 --> 37:33.585
Suspect in custody.
We're Code 4.

37:33.585 --> 37:35.462
Better bring in
the bomb squad.

37:35.462 --> 37:37.797
Someone brought a grenade
to the party.

37:37.797 --> 37:40.008
[ Breathing heavily ]

37:47.724 --> 37:50.185
You're welcome!
For what?

37:50.185 --> 37:53.104
Well, I created an Excel
spreadsheet for your expenses.

37:53.104 --> 37:55.148
I used something similar
when I first started on the job.

37:55.148 --> 37:56.733
It is super helpful.

37:56.733 --> 37:59.360
And I-I can send you
the app, as well.
Mm-hmm.

37:59.360 --> 38:01.654
And trust me.
You're gonna feel so gratified

38:01.654 --> 38:03.239
when you hit your target
at the end of the month,

38:03.239 --> 38:05.617
and you'll see that those, um --
those juices

38:05.617 --> 38:07.619
aren't on the daily budget.
Sorry.

38:07.619 --> 38:10.205
Mm.
Appreciate that, but...

38:10.205 --> 38:11.831
I talked to my mom
last night,

38:11.831 --> 38:14.125
and she's backing down on
the whole action-figure thing,

38:14.125 --> 38:15.168
so it's all good.

38:15.168 --> 38:18.421
Oh. So you're
taking her money again.

38:18.421 --> 38:20.465
Yeah, I-I just
can't live in poverty.

38:20.465 --> 38:22.050
Uh --

38:22.050 --> 38:24.427
It's not poverty.

38:24.427 --> 38:25.887
Aaron!

38:25.887 --> 38:27.639
[ Indistinct conversations,
siren wails in distance ]

38:27.639 --> 38:30.600
Hey, Bradford.

38:30.600 --> 38:33.394
Good job out there today.
Thanks.

38:33.394 --> 38:35.230
They're a good bunch
once you get to know them.

38:35.230 --> 38:37.690
Yeah.
I'll take your word for it.

38:37.690 --> 38:41.486
Nothing against Patrol, but...
Metro is a different beast.

38:41.486 --> 38:44.489
We get called in situations that
are already at a boiling point.

38:44.489 --> 38:47.826
That kind of stress
creates a special bond.

38:47.826 --> 38:49.244
And I'm on
the outside of that.

38:49.244 --> 38:52.747
And every single one of them
was, too, at some point.

38:52.747 --> 38:55.041
Give it a little time.

38:55.041 --> 38:56.835
Okay.

38:56.835 --> 38:58.670
You want to grab
a beer with us?

38:58.670 --> 39:00.296
Do I have a choice?

39:00.296 --> 39:02.632
It's tradition.
New guy buys a round.

39:02.632 --> 39:03.591
[ Chuckles ]

39:03.591 --> 39:05.134
Come on.

39:05.134 --> 39:08.263
[ Nightlands' "Whiplash"
playing ]

39:08.263 --> 39:10.431
Yes, I'm happy
to send over my references.

39:10.431 --> 39:13.476
And I can start
whenever you need me.

39:13.476 --> 39:15.687
Thanks.

39:15.687 --> 39:18.314
Hey. You looking
for another job?

39:18.314 --> 39:20.942
Uh, Cosmo's parents are
definitely getting a divorce.

39:20.942 --> 39:22.694
Sonia wants to keep me on,
but she's not sure

39:22.694 --> 39:26.114
if she can afford it
with all the legal fees, so...

39:26.114 --> 39:29.784
You're not still worried about
having to move out, are you?

39:29.784 --> 39:31.828
I just don't want
to be a burden.

39:31.828 --> 39:32.912
You're not.

39:32.912 --> 39:35.373
Tamara, look.

39:35.373 --> 39:37.500
I get it. Your whole life,
you've been displaced

39:37.500 --> 39:40.086
from one home to another,
but that's over now.

39:40.086 --> 39:42.130
Girl, we're family.

39:42.130 --> 39:43.965
You couldn't get rid of me
if you tried.

39:43.965 --> 39:45.008
♪ To think too much ♪

39:45.008 --> 39:46.718
Thanks.

39:46.718 --> 39:48.511
But I will get
my own place eventually.

39:48.511 --> 39:50.638
Mm-hmm.
I don't plan
to be the weirdo roommate

39:50.638 --> 39:52.265
when you and Tim
start having babies.

39:52.265 --> 39:54.434
[ Inhales sharply ]
That's a long way off.

39:54.434 --> 39:55.852
But I don't know.
Maybe it could work out.

39:55.852 --> 39:57.562
I heard you're
a really good babysitter.

39:57.562 --> 39:59.772
[ Inhales sharply ]
You can't afford my rate.

39:59.772 --> 40:00.607
It's like that?

40:00.607 --> 40:02.358
It is.

40:02.358 --> 40:05.486
Okay. And you're really gonna
leave all your artwork behind?

40:05.486 --> 40:06.779
[ Indistinct conversation ]

40:06.779 --> 40:08.948
Monica: Wesley. Keep bothering
me and my associates,

40:08.948 --> 40:10.116
I'll happily
alert the press.

40:10.116 --> 40:11.492
Judge Rivas is dead.

40:11.492 --> 40:13.036
Yes, I heard.

40:13.036 --> 40:14.287
What happened?

40:14.287 --> 40:15.997
Heart attack.
[ Sighs ]

40:15.997 --> 40:19.876
But we both know that's a lie.
Elijah had him killed for you.

40:19.876 --> 40:21.461
That's ridiculous.

40:21.461 --> 40:23.713
He believed in you
when you were starting out.

40:23.713 --> 40:26.591
And for good reason.
I am an excellent lawyer --

40:26.591 --> 40:29.052
and profoundly litigious,
so watch the accusations.

40:29.052 --> 40:31.095
I did warn you.

40:31.095 --> 40:33.640
This is the price
of working for Elijah.

40:33.640 --> 40:35.266
Well, if you're done
mansplaining,

40:35.266 --> 40:36.851
I've got some actual
work to do.

40:36.851 --> 40:38.394
♪ Comparison's a thief ♪

40:38.394 --> 40:40.521
I guess Elijah finally
found his perfect lawyer,

40:40.521 --> 40:42.941
one with
as little morality as him.

40:42.941 --> 40:44.567
What I can't decide

40:44.567 --> 40:46.694
is if the woman that I
fell in love with in law school,

40:46.694 --> 40:49.322
who was kind and loving,

40:49.322 --> 40:52.325
is just gone
or if she never really existed.

40:52.325 --> 40:53.993
♪♪

40:53.993 --> 40:57.121
Were you always just a sociopath
putting on an act?

40:57.121 --> 41:00.917
♪♪

41:00.917 --> 41:02.669
He'll kill you, too,
you know.

41:02.669 --> 41:04.212
Eventually.

41:04.212 --> 41:06.172
♪ Better days are coming fast ♪

41:06.172 --> 41:08.383
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Another text.

41:08.383 --> 41:10.802
You are a hero
to firefighters everywhere.

41:10.802 --> 41:12.387
So they admit

41:12.387 --> 41:15.264
that police officers
aren't entirely useless.

41:15.264 --> 41:17.976
Today.
Tomorrow, the rivalry resumes.

41:17.976 --> 41:19.143
I'll take it.

41:19.143 --> 41:22.855
[ Laughs ]
[ Cellphone ringing ]

41:22.855 --> 41:23.815
Is that your mom again?

41:23.815 --> 41:25.650
Foxburg Memorial Hospital.

41:25.650 --> 41:27.193
Hello?

41:27.193 --> 41:28.987
Yes, this is he.

41:28.987 --> 41:31.239
♪♪

41:31.239 --> 41:33.116
I don't understand.

41:33.116 --> 41:36.577
♪♪

41:36.577 --> 41:38.371
Oh.

41:38.371 --> 41:39.956
Alright, thank you.

41:41.457 --> 41:43.793
What?

41:43.793 --> 41:45.378
♪♪

41:45.378 --> 41:47.547
My mom died.

41:47.547 --> 41:51.092
♪♪

41:55.972 --> 41:58.975
-- Captions by VITAC --

41:58.975 --> 42:06.899
♪♪

42:06.899 --> 42:14.741
♪♪

42:14.741 --> 42:22.707
♪♪
